Born Free co-founder Virginia McKenna celebrates her 95th birthday today. To mark the occasion we are sharing some of our favourite photos of Virginia with some of the animals she has helped to save.

Here Virginia is pictured with an orphaned chimpanzee at the Esther Winstone Centre in Kenya - one of the many projects of the Virginia McKenna Animal Rescue Trust. The Trust was founded following Virginia’s work with hyrax, which led to the development of a rescue and release centre for orphaned and confiscated wildlife. To date over 100,000 animals have been cared for at the Trust.

We are so grateful to Virginia for her lifelong dedication to the animals that she loves.
